\vert _{t_n} + {\mbox{O}}(h^3).
\end{displaymath}"></td>
<td width=3D"10" align=3D"RIGHT">
(13)</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<br clear=3D"ALL"><p></p>
However, we know from the IVP (Eq. 6)  that=20

<!-- MATH: $dy/dt  =3D f(y,t)$ -->
<i>dy</i>/<i>dt</i>  =3D <i>f</i>(<i>y</i>,<i>t</i>) so that=20
<br><p></p>
<div align=3D"CENTER">

<!-- MATH: \begin{equation}
\frac{d^2y}{dt^2} =3D \frac{df(y,t)}{dt} =3D \frac{\partial f}{\partial t} =
+ \frac{\partial f}{\partial y}\frac{dy}{dt} =3D
\frac{\partial f}{\partial t} + f \frac{\partial f}{\partial y}.
\end{equation} -->

<table width=3D"100%" align=3D"CENTER">
<tbody><tr valign=3D"MIDDLE"><td align=3D"CENTER" nowrap=3D""><img width=3D=
"354" height=3D"52" src=3D"https://web.mit.edu/10.001/Web/Course_Notes/Diff=
erential_Equations_Notes/img37.gif" alt=3D"\begin{displaymath}\frac{d^2y}{d=
t^2} =3D \frac{df(y,t)}{dt} =3D \frac{\partial f}{\p...
...rac{\partial f}{\partial t} + f \frac{\partial f}{\partial y}.
\end{displaymath}"></td>
<td width=3D"10" align=3D"RIGHT">
(14)</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<br clear=3D"ALL"><p></p>
So from the above analysis, i.e., Eqs. 14 and 15, we get=20
<br><p></p>
<div align=3D"CENTER">

<!-- MATH: \begin{equation}
y_{n+1} =3D y_n + h f(y_n,t_n) + \frac{h^2}{2} \left[ \frac{\partial f}{\pa=
rtial t} + f \frac{\partial f}{\partial y}\right](y_n,t_n)
+ {\mbox{O}}(h^3).

\end{equation} -->

<table width=3D"100%" align=3D"CENTER">
<tbody><tr valign=3D"MIDDLE"><td align=3D"CENTER" nowrap=3D""><img width=3D=
"468" height=3D"54" src=3D"https://web.mit.edu/10.001/Web/Course_Notes/Diff=
erential_Equations_Notes/img38.gif" alt=3D"\begin{displaymath}y_{n+1} =3D y=
_n + h f(y_n,t_n) + \frac{h^2}{2} \left[ \frac{\pa...
...ac{\partial f}{\partial y}\right](y_n,t_n)
+ {\mbox{O}}(h^3).
\end{displaymath}"></td>
<td width=3D"10" align=3D"RIGHT">
(15)</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<br clear=3D"ALL"><p></p>
However, the term <i>k</i><sub>2</sub> in the proposed RK method of Eq. 13 =
can be expanded correct to O(<i>h</i><sup>3</sup>) as=20
<br>
<div align=3D"CENTER">

