<br clear=3D"ALL"><p></p>
Now, substituting for <i>k</i><sub>2</sub> from Eq. 17 in Eq. 13, we get   =
            =20
<br><p></p>
<div align=3D"CENTER">

<!-- MATH: \begin{equation}
y_{n+1} =3D y_n + (a+b) h f(y_n,t_n) + bh^2(\alpha \frac {\partial f}{\part=
ial t} + \beta f
