<p>
In a similar fashion Runge-Kutta methods of higher order can be developed. =
One of the most widely used methods for the=20
solution of IVPs is the <em>fourth order Runge-Kutta</em> (RK4) technique. =
The LTE of this method is order <i>h</i><sup>5</sup>.=20
The method is given below.=20
<br>
</p><div align=3D"CENTER">

<!-- MATH: \begin{eqnarray}
&& k_1 =3D hf(y_n,t_n)\nonumber \\
&& k_2 =3D hf(y_n+k_1/2, t_n + h/2) \nonumber \\
&& k_3 =3D hf(y_n+k_2/2, t_n + h/2) \:\: \: {\mbox{Fourth Order Runge-Kutta=
 Method (RK4).}} \nonumber \\
&& k_4 =3D h(y_n+k_3, t_n + h) \nonumber \\
&& y_{n+1} =3D y_n + (k_1 + 2k_2 + 2k_3 + k_4)/6.
\end{eqnarray} -->

